  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Joseph Lupton sent a box of contributions to the anti-slavery fair by one of the Warren &amp; Thayer packet ships. He refers to the &quot;monetary crisis through which you are now passing,&quot; i.e. the business depression of 1857. He says that one of his friends is in Lucknow, now under siege by the Indian rebels. Joseph Lupton has moved to a new address.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">On pages 2-3 of this manuscript, there is a separate letter from Elizabeth Lupton to Maria Weston Chapman, October 1, 1857; above the salutation, it is marked &quot;Copy.&quot;</subfield>
